; - Frequency: 3-30 MHz HF band
; - Feed: Center-fed monopole (segment 6 of 12)
; - Mounting: Belly-mounted (standard helicopter HF position)
;
; Bottom-Mounted Antenna Benefits:
; - Omnidirectional coverage (360° radiation pattern)
; - No side blindness for tactical operations
; - Ground communication when hovering/landing
; - Pilot access for maintenance/emergency
; - Clear of rotor interference
; - Tactical advantage for close air support
;
; Expected HF Performance:
; - Gain: 2-6 dBi (typical for HF whip on helicopter)
; - Range: 100-300 km (long-range tactical communication)
; - VSWR: <2:1 with proper matching network
; - Pattern: Omnidirectional with slight directivity
;
; UH-1 Military Operations:
; - Long-range tactical communication
; - Strategic helicopter operations
; - Ground-to-air communication
; - Multi-role military helicopter
;
; This configuration represents a realistic UH-1 Huey
